      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OVER REACTION (2) is an honest type in the frame at 15 of 30 starts including last time when second (22.84) over 400m at this track. Has never missed the frame at the trip from four starts. Looks well placed here and should prove hard to beat again. MELLCAT BAD BOY (4) broke a string of placings finishing in the money two on end before a last start fifth (20.07) at Goulburn. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Has the ability to give this a shake. MIDNIGHT STAR (3) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 3.5 lengths at Richmond in a handy 22.98 beating Dandy Redeemer. Fair draw can see a good run and in form and has the ability. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Has definite claims. SASSY CROSSED (1) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
